data.title: "Dancing with the Stars: All-Stars" finale
data.meta_description: Melissa Rycroft and Tony Dovolani were crowned champions of "Dancing With the Stars: All-Stars" on Nov. 27, 2012
data.text:
Melissa Rycroft and Tony Dovolani were crowned champions of "Dancing with the Stars: All-Stars," Nov. 27, 2012.

Melissa Rycroft and Tony Dovolani were crowned champions of this all-star season, on the season finale of "Dancing With the Stars: All-Stars," Nov. 27, 2012.

Pictures: "Dancing with the Stars: All-Stars"

Timeline: Past "DWTS" competitors and champions

Melissa Rycroft and Tony Dovolani were crowned champions of this all-star season.

Pictures: "Dancing with the Stars: All-Stars"

Timeline: Past "DWTS" competitors and champions

In the final element of the competition, the three finalists performed an Instant Dance routine. They were given their music and dance style just minutes before they performed live to complete the judges' scores, on the season finale of "Dancing with the Stars: All-Stars," on Nov. 27, 2012.

Pictures: "Dancing with the Stars: All-Stars"

Second-place finishers Derek Hough and Shawn Johnson are seen here with Tom Bergeron in the final element of the competition; the three finalists performed an instant dance routine on the season finale of "Dancing With the Stars: All-Stars," Nov. 27, 2012.

Pictures: "Dancing with the Stars: All-Stars"

From left, Tom Bergeron, Brooke Burke Charvet, Kelly Monaco and Valentin Chmerkovskiy. After 10 weeks of competitive dancing, one couple was crowned champions of "Dancing With the Stars: All-Stars," Nov. 27, 2012.
